<a href="https://www.vacationstogo.com/ticker.cfm?l=25&r=0&jpw=50&source=cruisemm&csp=K6rK6r&nr=cus_K6r_int&mmz=1">See dates and prices</a>.<br>
<br>
As always, all offers in this newsletter are for new bookings only and
subject to availability. Restrictions may apply, and some free amenities
and shipboard credits may apply only to eligible rates. Past guests of
some cruise lines may see better rates on select sailings.<br>
<br><hr><br><!-- End of intro -->
I'm excited to tell you about a concept that is becoming increasingly
popular in the cruise industry -- <b>Ship-Within-A-Ship</b> -- that
offers the intimate ambiance, luxurious amenities and personalized
service of a small cruise ship or yacht within a large vessel.<br>
<br>
Guests booked into these elite staterooms typically have keycard entry
to designated areas, venues and accommodations aboard the ship. These
often include private access to exclusive restaurants, lounges and a
sundeck with a pool and hot tub, along with upgraded accommodations
featuring luxury bath products and fine linens. Additional amenities
often include concierge services, a dedicated butler, as well as
priority check-in, boarding and disembarkation.<br>
<br>
Below, I've highlighted some popular Ship-Within-A-Ship concepts offered
by several cruise lines. We recommend calling us to verify prices and
availability, as these accommodations are only available in select
categories and are highly sought after.<br>
<br>
<b>Sanctuary Collection</b> by <b>Princess Cruises</b> offers an
elevated experience for guests booked into Sanctuary accommodations
(suite, mini-suite and balcony) aboard the Sun Princess and Star
Princess. These staterooms include access to the Sanctuary Club -- a
top-deck adults-only poolside retreat -- and a private restaurant, as
well as Princess Premier, an all-inclusive package with premium
beverages, specialty and casual dining, gratuities, internet access and
more. Guests staying in a Sanctuary Suite also enjoy exclusive access to
the Suite Lounge. To view sailings with staterooms in the Sanctuary
Collection,
<a href="https://www.vacationstogo.com/ticker.cfm?s=1228,1250&jpw=50&source=cruisemm&csp=K6rK6r&nr=cus_K6r_int&mmz=1">click here</a>.<br>
<br>
<b>The Haven</b> by <b>Norwegian</b> is a top-of-the-ship enclave
featuring luxurious accommodations and a private sundeck with a pool and
hot tub. Guests booked in The Haven accommodations enjoy access to an
exclusive lounge and restaurant on select ships. Other highlights
include 24-hour butler service, a dedicated concierge and priority
embarkation, tendering and disembarkation. To view sailings with
staterooms in The Haven,
<a href="https://www.vacationstogo.com/ticker.cfm?ns=vtg,mm,G3v,haven&mpct=84&jpw=50&source=cruisemm&csp=K6rK6r&nr=cus_K6r_int&mmz=1">click here</a>.<br>
<br>
<b>Yacht Club</b> by <b>MSC Cruises</b> is an exclusive private oasis,
featuring elegant suites, a dedicated restaurant, lounge, pools and a
sundeck. The Yacht Club boasts unparalleled service, including a
concierge team, 24-hour butler service, and priority embarkation and
disembarkation. Passengers enjoy an all-inclusive package with premium
beverages, internet access and complimentary entry to the Thermal Suite.
To view sailings with staterooms in the Yacht Club,
<a href="https://www.vacationstogo.com/ticker.cfm?ns=vtg,mm,G3v,yachtclub&mpct=52&jpw=50&source=cruisemm&csp=K6rK6r&nr=cus_K6r_int&mmz=1">click here</a>.<br>
<br>
<b>The Retreat</b> by <b>Celebrity Cruises</b> is designed for guests
booked into select suites, featuring exclusive access to a private
restaurant, lounge and a sundeck with a pool and hot tub on select
ships. Guests can expect top-tier hospitality with a dedicated butler, a
concierge team and priority departure and embarkation at most
destinations. The Retreat also includes perks such as premium drinks and
internet access for certain suite categories. To view sailings with
staterooms in The Retreat,
<a href="https://www.vacationstogo.com/ticker.cfm?ns=vtg,mm,G3v,retreat&mpct=34&jpw=50&source=cruisemm&csp=K6rK6r&nr=cus_K6r_int&mmz=1">click here</a>.<br>
<br>
<b>The Queens Grill</b> and <b>Princess Grill</b> by <b>Cunard</b> are
exclusive to guests booked in elegant Grill Suite accommodations,
featuring access to private restaurants and the Grills Lounge.
Passengers will experience world-class service with a concierge and have
priority embarkation and disembarkation. Both Grill Suites include an
array of perks, such as the traditional Afternoon Tea. The Queens Grill
is considered the most elite of the two and offers additional benefits
such as butler service. To view sailings with staterooms in the Grill
Suites,
<a href="https://www.vacationstogo.com/ticker.cfm?s=524,1221,246,407&jpw=50&source=cruisemm&csp=K6rK6r&nr=cus_K6r_int&mmz=1">click here</a>.<br>
<br>
Additional cruise lines also offer variations of the Ship-Within-A-Ship
concept. While amenities may differ, guests can still enjoy elevated
service and exclusive access to venues. A few examples are Holland
America's Neptune Suites, Royal Caribbean's Suite Class, Disney Cruise
Line's Concierge cabins and Carnival's Havana cabins.<br>
<br><hr><br><!-- End of intro -->
